<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1855,1988]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1855,1880]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Bronze with metallic purple; hind wing absent; pronotum with lateral callus separated by shallow punctured depression only at basal part, with dense punctures near basal lateral side; elytron with punctures forming 
<number box="[1422,1436,1892,1916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" value="9.0">9</number>
irregular single striae; inner edge of epipleura with 
<number box="[754,768,1928,1952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" value="3.0">3</number>
bristles; Hypomera smooth, without punctures; pygidium without longitudinal depression medially.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,336,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Description</emphasis>
(based on 
<typeStatus box="[457,561,151,175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">holotype</typeStatus>
): 
<emphasis box="[580,659,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Colour</emphasis>
: Bronze with metallic purple; two basal segment of antennae reddish brown; compound eyes bronze; apex of mandible, last segment of maxillary palpi, last segment of labial palpi, apex of onychium reddish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,319]" box="[197,712,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
Body length: 
<quantity box="[349,452,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.52" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="5.52">5.52 mm</quantity>
, body width: 
<quantity box="[604,708,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.96" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="2.96">2.96 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,319]" box="[197,1200,295,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
Body elongate-ovoid (
<figureCitation box="[447,513,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1277,1300]" captionTargetBox="[171,1404,393,1250]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,373,1256]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chrysolina gyacaensis, sp. nov. A. Habitus; B. Left antenna (male); C. Aedeagus, lateral view; D. Aedeagus apex, dorsal view; E. Tarsus, male; scale bar: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200888/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[500,513,295,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A), moderate large, convex in lateral view; hind wing absent.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200888/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" targetBox="[171,1404,393,1250]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1277,1330]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
