<emphasis box="[280,510,1278,1300]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Chrysolina gyacaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[522,602,1278,1299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[522,602,1278,1299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A. Habitus; B. Left antenna (male); C. Aedeagus, lateral view; D. Aedeagus apex, dorsal view; E. Tarsus, male; scale bar: 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1375,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis box="[197,257,1375,1399]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Head</emphasis>
: Clypeus with sparse pubescence, moderate and small punctures; frons shagreened, with dense and moderate punctures; coronal suture present, frontal suture present, but very thin, shallow; vertex with sparse and moderate punctures; compound eyes oblong, dorso-ventral eye length 
<quantity box="[889,991,1447,1471]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="0.22">0.22 mm</quantity>
, interocular distance 
<quantity box="[1230,1332,1447,1471]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.28" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="1.28">1.28 mm</quantity>
; distance from antennal insertion to eye: 
<quantity box="[501,604,1483,1507]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="0.19">0.19 mm</quantity>
; distance from antennal insertion to clypeus: 
<quantity box="[1112,1215,1483,1507]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="0.08">0.08 mm</quantity>
; mandible with two denticles, outer surface with sparse pubescence, with moderate and dense punctures; third segment of maxillary palpi shorter than fourth, apex of fourth segment of maxillary palpi truncate; antennae with basal segments narrow, widening from segments 
<number box="[438,519,1591,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="8.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="6.0">6 to 11</number>
, antennal segment (
<number box="[746,802,1591,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="6.0" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="1.0">1â€“11</number>
) length (in millimeter): 
<number box="[1079,1128,1591,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="0.32">0.32</number>
: 
<number box="[1151,1200,1591,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="0.16">0.16</number>
: 
<number box="[1225,1274,1591,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="0.24">0.24</number>
: 
<number box="[1298,1347,1591,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="0.24">0.24</number>
: 
<number box="[1371,1420,1591,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="0.24">0.24</number>
: 
<number box="[151,200,1627,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="0.24">0.24</number>
: 
<number box="[221,270,1627,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="0.16">0.16</number>
: 
<number box="[292,341,1627,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="0.16">0.16</number>
: 
<number box="[363,412,1627,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="0.16">0.16</number>
: 
<number box="[434,483,1627,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="0.16">0.16</number>
: 
<number box="[505,554,1627,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="0.36">0.36</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[569,636,1627,1651]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1277,1300]" captionTargetBox="[171,1404,393,1250]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,373,1256]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chrysolina gyacaensis, sp. nov. A. Habitus; B. Left antenna (male); C. Aedeagus, lateral view; D. Aedeagus apex, dorsal view; E. Tarsus, male; scale bar: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200888/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[622,636,1627,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1375,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis box="[197,308,1664,1687]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Pronotum</emphasis>
: Length: 
<quantity box="[418,522,1663,1687]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.60 mm</quantity>
; width: 
<quantity box="[613,717,1663,1687]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.80 mm</quantity>
. Sides of anterior and posterior angles without setigerous punctures; central disc with moderate and sparse punctures, similar to those of head; with lateral callus separated by shallow punctured depression only at basal part; with dense punctures near basal lateral side; lateral punctures of disc small and sparse.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1375,1975]" box="[197,747,1807,1831]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicName box="[197,307,1807,1831]" class="Trilobita" family="Styginidae" genus="Scutellum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Corynexochida" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[197,307,1807,1831]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Scutellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: Sub-triangular, with sparse punctures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1375,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis box="[197,267,1843,1867]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="36">Elytra</emphasis>
: Suture length: 
<quantity box="[456,562,1843,1867]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.16" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="4.16">4.16 mm</quantity>
; width of elytra: 
<quantity box="[766,872,1843,1867]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.44" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="3.44">3.44 mm</quantity>
; elytron with punctures forming 
<number box="[1255,1269,1843,1867]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="9.0">9</number>
regular single striae, sutural stria present, punctures larger than those of side of pronotum; interspaces of elytral striae with very fine and sparse punctures, with horizontal wrinkles especially on basal part; epipleuron horizontal, with outer bor- der sharp, inner edge of epipleura with 
<number box="[591,605,1951,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
sparse bristles apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[197,250,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Legs</emphasis>
: Femora and tibiae with sparse, moderate punctures, sparse pubescence, apices of tibiae with dense pubescence; tarsomere 
<number box="[411,419,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
of male protarsus enlarged; hind tarsi entirely pubescent beneath; relative lengths of hind tarsomeres: 
<number box="[287,301,223,247]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="5.0">5</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[318,328,223,247]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[346,359,223,247]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="3.0">3</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[377,392,223,247]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="2.0">2</number>
, tarsomere 
<number box="[522,536,223,247]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="5.0">5</number>
not ventrally toothed (
<figureCitation box="[791,858,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1277,1300]" captionTargetBox="[171,1404,393,1250]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,373,1256]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chrysolina gyacaensis, sp. nov. A. Habitus; B. Left antenna (male); C. Aedeagus, lateral view; D. Aedeagus apex, dorsal view; E. Tarsus, male; scale bar: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200888/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[844,858,223,247]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[197,265,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Venter</emphasis>
: Hypomera smooth, without punctures; middle part of intercoxal prosternal process more than half width of apex; prosternal process with dense and moderate punctures, truncate and not emarginate behind; mesoventrite shorter than prosternum between coxae; metaventrite with dense, moderate punctures, with sparse pubescence; metaventrite shorter than prosternum; mesepisternum, mesepimeron and metepisternum without punctures; abdomen with dense, moderate punctures, sparse pubescence; last abdominal sternite of male without emargination; pygidium with arcuate apex, without longitudinal depression medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,752]" box="[197,1421,476,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[197,478,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Median lobe of aedeagus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[494,571,476,500]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1277,1300]" captionTargetBox="[171,1404,393,1250]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,373,1256]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chrysolina gyacaensis, sp. nov. A. Habitus; B. Left antenna (male); C. Aedeagus, lateral view; D. Aedeagus apex, dorsal view; E. Tarsus, male; scale bar: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200888/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
Figs. 
<number box="[558,571,476,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
Câ€“D): Basal part as wide as apex; curved in lateral view. Flagellum slender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,752]" box="[197,398,511,535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,548,572]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
Members of the new species are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lopatin" authorityName="Lopatin" box="[894,1202,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chrysolina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauroi">
<emphasis box="[894,1106,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Chrysolina mauroi</emphasis>
Lopatin
</taxonomicName>
, but the punctures of pronotum are different: in the new species, the lateral callus is present only at base in, 
<taxonomicName box="[1130,1342,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chrysolina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauroi">
<emphasis box="[1130,1342,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Chrysolina mauroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the lateral callus is present on the whole length; and the aedeagus is also different.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
